{
  "doc_id": "33236",
  "text": "Mishra et al. [CITATION_1] introduced Solar Photovoltaics (SPV) instead of a dc power source of the impressed-current CP system. Since the output of the SPV is a dc voltage, it can eliminate the rectifier that is found in conventional impressed CP systems. The SVP-based CP system simply replaces the dc power source of the conventional CP system with SVP power; it does not support DAQ and remote monitoring function, so routine manual inspection is still required.",
  "correct_citation": {
